  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You gain a wondrous appearance, granting temporary hitpoints to your allies.</p>\n<details>\n<summary style=\"padding-bottom:8px\"><strong>Full Description</strong></summary>\n<blockquote style=\"font-style:normal\">\n<p>When you join the College of Glamour at 3rd level, you gain the ability to weave a song of fey magic that imbues your allies with vigor and speed.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action, you can expend one use of your @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.7Q7X8BnKOsk2SXSt]{Bardic Inspiration} to grant yourself a wondrous appearance. When you do so, choose a number of creatures you can see and who can see you within 60 feet of you, up to a number equal to your <strong>Charisma modifier</strong> (minimum of one). Each of them gains <strong>5 temporary hit points</strong>. When a creature gains these temporary hit points, it can immediately use its reaction to move up to its speed, without provoking <strong>opportunity attacks</strong>.</p>\n<p>The number of temporary hit points increases when you reach certain levels in this class, increasing to 8 at 5th level, 11 at 10th level, and 14 at 15th level.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</details>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: When you add this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Bardic Inspiration.</em></p>\n</section>",
